PS :

    PRINT SNAPSHOT OF PROCESSES : ps

    PRINT SNAPSHOT OF ALL PROCESSES BY CURRENT USER : ps a

    PRINT SNAPSHOT OF PROCESSES WITH EVERYTHING : ps -e OR ps -A

    PRINT SNAPSHOT OF ALL PROCESSES BY ALL USERS : ps ax

    PRINT SNAPSHOT OF ALL USERS ALL PROCESSES : ps aux

    ABOVE THINGS IN DETAILED LONG FORMAT : ps axl 

    ABOVE THINGS IN HEIRARCHY OR FORCED FORMAT : ps fax

    SEE PROCESS TREE : ps -fHe

    ABOVE THINGS IN HEIRARCHY AND FORCED WITH LINES : ps -fe --forest

    ABOVE THINGS IN EXTRA FULL FORMAT : ps -F

    SORT BY DESIRED FIELD  : ps aux --sort -field_-pfield


PROCESS TERMINATION : 

    STOP A PROCESS : kill -9 PID

    KILL A PROCESS : kill PID

    KILL ON TOP : press k AND_THEN PID AND_THEN confirm

    KILL ON JOBS RUN BY SPECIFIC USER : sudo killall -u UserName

    KILL BY PROCESS NAME : pkill ProcessName

    LIST SIGNALS FOR KILL : kill -l 


TOP :

    SUMMARY DATA AREA :

        INTERACTIVE DETAILS OF ALL ONGOING PROCESSES : top

        HIDE TOP MOST LINE IN VIEW : press l

        SEE INFO FOR ALL CPUS : press 1

        CPU USAGE GRAPH : press t

        RAM AND SWAP GRAPH : press m

        CHANGE MEMORY UNITS KB MB GB TB : press E

    COLUMN HEADERS AND TASK INFO PROCESSE LIST : 

        CHANGE REFRESH RATE OF TOP IN SECONDS : press d OR spacebar or enter

        FILTER BY USERNAME : press u and UserName     

    NICE : 

        CHANGE NICE VALUE : 
            
            FOR TOP : press r and PID 
            REASSIGN NICE VALUE : sudo renice -n Value -p PID 
            ASSIGN WHILE RUUNING Commands : sudo nice -n Value Commands


MANAGEMENT : 

    SHOW ACTIVE JOBS ON CURRENT TERMINAL : jobs

    RESUME JOB TO FOREGROUND : fg %JOB_ID

    RESUME JOB TO BACKGROUND : bg %JOB_ID

    RUN JOB IN BACKGROUND : Commands &

    LIST JOBS and PID : jobs -l

    RUN SCRIPT FREE OF TERMINAL AND OUTPUT IN NOHUP.OUT FILE : nohup /Path/ScriptName & 

